sPerShareFromContinuingAndDiscontinuedOperations><in-bse-fin:DebtEquityRatio contextRef="OneD" unitRef="pure" decimals="INF">0.0116</in-bse-fin:DebtEquityRatio><in-bse-fin:DebtServiceCoverageRatio contextRef="OneD" unitRef="pure" decimals="INF">0.0299</in-bse-fin:DebtServiceCoverageRatio><in-bse-fin:InterestServiceCoverageRatio contextRef="OneD" unitRef="pure" decimals="INF">0.0166</in-bse-fin:InterestServiceCoverageRatio><in-bse-fin:DisclosureOfNotesOnFinancialResultsExplanatoryTextBlock contextRef="OneD">Please note that the point no. 1 Income Revenue from Operations for quarter and six months ended 30th September, 2024 consists of Sales – Rs. 1120.50 &amp; Rs. 2260.17 &amp; Other Operating Income – Rs. 7.06 and Rs. 16.63 respectively &lt;BR&gt; 
The above consolidated unaudited financial results for the quarter and six months ended September 30, 2024 have been reviewed and recommended for adoption by the Audit Committee to the Board of Directors and have been approved by the Board at its meeting held on October 22, 2024. &lt;BR&gt; 
During the quarter ended June 30, 2023, the Holding Company had initiated the process to restructure its operations at its Bharuch Textile Division business ('Division') which includes outsourcing some of the material from the third party instead of manufacturing it in the plant. Subsequently, during the quarter ended March 31, 2024, Board of Directors of the Holding Company had approved the proposal for discontinuation of complete operations of the Division. Accordingly, results of the said Division is disclosed as discontinued operations in the financial results and results of quarter and six months ended September 30, 2023 has been restated. As the operations are discontinued, during the previous year, the Holding Company has assessed the recoverability of Property, plant and equipment and other assets of the said Division and recognized a provision aggregating to Rs. 214.00 Crores as Loss on measurement to net realizable value.          &lt;BR&gt; 
'Other operating income for the year ended March 31, 2024 include gain on sale of Transferable Development Rights (TDR) amounting to Rs. 201.68 crores. &lt;BR&gt; 
The Group is organised into business divisions based on its products and services and has four reportable segments, as follows: &lt;BR&gt; 
"Textiles" include Yarn &amp; Fabric (Discontinued operations) and Viscose Filament Yarn &amp; Tyre Yarn (Rayon) &lt;BR&gt; 
"Pulp and Paper" include Pulp, Writing &amp; Printing paper, Tissue paper and Multilayer packaging board. &lt;BR&gt; 
  "Real Estate" includes Residential projects, Leased properties and Investment properties of the Group. &lt;BR&gt; 
"Others" include Salt works and Chemicals. &lt;BR&gt; 
